on moss snakes. Now make level 1 take 10-20 minutes when grinding on Krups in chef. <br><br>Another example, level 44 takes an average of maybe 15 hours? make it take 30. This of course would start to get fairly insane with level 59 etc. <br><br>How much power would this add to the class?<br>Well, alot... but not quite as much as it seems. If needed, they could even cap the level at which you can gain with the new class. even as low as 30, or 46. <br><br>So when you get your title, you may select a class, you instantly gain any inherant abilities of that class, and gain exp with that class with the same time of bar you use for AA. let me use an example. <br><br>Lets say I am a 60 rogue, and have just attained my maruader title... ok, for some reason, I want to be a shadowknight. I type some BS in such as /train shadowknight.<br>I now have the ability to Harm touch(for 11 dmg, since im lvl 1), able to raise 2hs, 2hp, 2hb etc. (they would have to code *SOMETHING* to prevent us from backstabbing with @#%$ like tantors tusk though heh.) and able to equip any SK gear, but with the same level requirements for the casting as your SK's level is prolly. Once you select a class, you canot just get those benifits, and then switch... if you switch your class, you lose all the abilities you earned. which is why they should make the training command some wierd long thing that you could not accidently type. <br><br>Well, anyway.. not saying they *should* do this, or even it would be a good idea... just saying that I think it would be fun. Wondering what everyone else thinks. <br><br>and if so, what class would you go for offhand(don't think about it too much). I am thinking rogue/bard, rog/ench, or rog/sham. this actually wouldn't be quite as overpowering for raids as it seems, but yeah.. it would make exp grinding, soloing, dueling against someone without it.. pretty trivial. still neat though.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valig